# Week 1 Azure Foundation Lab

**Author:** Nghiem Nguyen
**Date:** January 16th, 2026

## Overview
This document summarizes the Azure resourcs built in Week 1 as part of my Cloud Support portfolio.

## Resource Group
**Name:** Week1-Lab-RG
**Region:** Central US
**Purpose:** Logical container for all Week 1 lab resources
**Notes:** All future resources (VM, Storage) deployed in this group

## Virtual Machine
**Name:** Week1-VM1
**OS:** Windows Server 2025 Datacenter x64 Gen2
**Size:** Standard_D2s (2 VCPU, 8 GiB memory)
**Public Inbound Port:** RDP (3389) for lab access
**Cost Management:** VM stopped (deallocated) when not in use 
**Purpose:** Lab environment to simulate a cloud support scenario

## Storage Account
**Name:** week1labstorage01
**Region:** Central US
**Type:** Azure Blob Storage
**Purpose:** Store lab data, backups, and artifacts
**Notes:** Created inside WEek1-Lab_RG

##Lessons Learned
Always check VM size options; free tier options may not appear in the portal.
Stopping (deallocating) VMs in critical to control costs.
Resource grouping makes it easier to organize and manage multiple lab assests.

